ðŸ“˜ Explanation of Each Component
1. Interface & Exceptions * ConverterService Defines the core contract for the conversion logic:

double convert(double amount, String from, String to);

InvalidCurrencyException Custom exception class that handles errors when an unsupported or incorrect currency code is entered.

2. Abstraction & Inheritance (Rate Providers) * RateProvider (Abstract Class) The base template for any system that provides exchange rates.

APIRateProvider (Child Class) Inherits from RateProvider. It contains the logic to connect to the ExchangeRate-API and fetch real-time data using HttpURLConnection.

3. Service Implementation & Polymorphism * CurrencyConverter Implements the ConverterService. It is polymorphic because it can work with any class that extends RateProvider.

4. Database Layer (JDBC) * DBHelper Handles the "Smart Setup." It checks if converterdb exists and creates it automatically using the root password provided by the user.

ConversionDAO Data Access Object that handles the SQL INSERT operations to save history into the MySQL table.

5. Main Entry Point * SmartCurrencyConverter The driver class. It manages the user interface (Scanner), initializes the database system, and triggers the conversion flow.

ðŸ—ƒ Database Blueprint
Even though the code creates the table automatically, the schema is:

SQL

CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS converterdb;
USE converterdb;

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS conversion_history (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    amount DOUBLE,
    source VARCHAR(10),
    target VARCHAR(10),
    result DOUBLE,
    time TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
